// Multi-hop schema-rooted dispatch: a 3-segment FnCall path
// (`o.customer.greet()`) walks the prefix `o.customer` through the
// inference engine, lands on `Schema("User")`, and resolves the last
// segment as a method on that schema. The 2-segment receiver form is
// the legacy case; this fixture pins the n>2 generalization.
#schema User {
    String name: *
} with {
    greet() -> String: f"hello ${self.name}"
}

#schema Order {
    User customer: *
}

#main(Order o)
{ String s: o.customer.greet() }
